data.Name: Lil Gotit
data.Bio: Semaja Zair Render (born August 6, 1999), popularly known as Lil Gotit, is an American recording artist from Cleveland Ave., Atlanta, Georgia, who started making music at a young age with his older brother Lil Keed. The two of them made their first song, “Trap Bunkin,” together. Gotit has had his music played at various clubs in Atlanta. The name Lil Gotit is derived from his original rap name, Maja Got It, a nickname inspired by him “having everything.” He has cited Young Thug as his mentor. Read more on Last.fm

data.Name: Lil Gnar
data.Bio: A rapper who was written up in Elevator Mag for his music video "Ride Wit Da Fye" in November 2017. He's also notable for his project, Big Bag Gnar Shit. His real name is Caleb. Originally from California, he would later move to Atlanta, Georgia. He spoke to his dad for the first time in several years in April 2017. Before Fame, he got his start with fashion and skateboarding with his brand GNARCOTIC, which he started in 2013. His nickname came from his life mantra when skating "Gnarly." Read more on Last.fm

data.Name: Lil Keed
data.Bio: Raqhid Jevon Render (born March 16, 1998), known professionally as Lil Keed, is an American rapper and songwriter. He is currently signed to Young Thug's YSL Records and 300 Entertainment. Read more on Last.fm

data.Name: Lil Tracy
data.Bio: Jazz Ishmael Butler (born October 3, 1995), known professionally as Lil Tracy or simply Tracy, is an American rapper, singer and songwriter. He is best known for his collaborations with the late rapper Lil Peep. Butler started to make music when he was 15 before moving to Los Angeles, California (without alerting his parents) to focus more on his music career and due to being homeless. Butler originally started rapping under the name "Yung Bruh", releasing several mixtapes under the Thraxxhouse collective. Read more on Last.fm

data.Name: Lil Mosey
data.Bio: Lathan Moses Echols (born January 25, 2002), known professionally as Lil Mosey, is an American rapper, singer, and songwriter. He first gained mainstream success with his song "Noticed", which peaked at #80 on the Billboard Hot 100. He dropped his debut mixtape Northsbest in 2018, which was eventually certified Gold. data.Name: Smokepurpp
data.Bio: Omar Pineiro (born May 15, 1997), known professionally as Smokepurpp (or Purpp), is an American rapper from Miami, Florida. Pineiro released his first music video "It’s Nothin" with Lil Ominous on September 23, 2014. Pineiro initially found success on the audio distribution platform SoundCloud in 2016. His earliest songs on SoundCloud date back to July of 2015. Popular associated acts include Lil Pump, XXXTENTACION, and Swag Hollywood. Smokepurpp and Lil Pump perform often together as Gucci Gang. Read more on Last.fm
